modules.description: This module creates and configures interactive timelines with customizable display options, supporting event creation and media integration. It works with JavaScript objects and custom types for dates, media, text, and events, allowing structured timeline data to be built and rendered in web applications. Concrete use cases include embedding historical event timelines, interactive stories, or chronological data visualizations directly in web pages using OCaml.

This module defines JSON encodings for timeline-related data types including dates, text, media, slides, eras, and full timelines. Each value provides direct serialization to and from JSON for its corresponding type. It is used to convert timeline structures to JSON format for storage or transmission, and to parse JSON input into typed OCaml values representing timeline elements.

This module constructs timeline data structures with precise date handling, text formatting, and media embedding. It creates slides, eras, and full timelines using typed values for dates, text, media URLs, and display properties. Concrete use cases include building interactive historical timelines with annotated events and media-rich entries.

This module defines data structures for representing timelines, including dates with optional precision, text elements, media objects, slides, and eras. It supports building rich, interactive timelines with structured data for display in a timeline visualization. Concrete use cases include creating historical timelines with media, annotating events with precise or approximate dates, and organizing events into eras with start and end points.

This module builds interactive timelines with structured data, supporting precise date handling, media integration, and customizable display properties. It provides data types for dates, text, media, slides, and eras, along with operations to construct and serialize timelines to JSON for storage or transmission. You can create historical timelines with annotated events, embed images or videos, and define time ranges with exact or approximate dates. Example uses include interactive storytelling, chronological data visualizations, and media-rich educational timelines displayed in web applications.
